ZH: 选民在选举期间扮演非常重要的角色。
EN: Voters play a crucial role during elections.

ZH: 选民在每个国家都享有投票的权利。
EN: Voters have the right to vote in every country.

ZH: 选民应该了解候选人的政策和立场。
EN: Voters should be aware of the policies and positions of the candidates.

ZH: 选民可以通过投票来影响政府决策。
EN: Voters can influence government decisions through voting.

ZH: 选民的意见反映了社会的声音。
EN: Voters' opinions reflect the voice of the society.

ZH: 选民可以选择支持自己认同的政党。
EN: Voters can choose to support the political party they identify with.

ZH: 选民的投票结果决定了选举的胜负。
EN: Voters' voting results determine the outcome of the election.

ZH: 选民有责任参与选举过程。
EN: Voters have a responsibility to participate in the electoral process.

ZH: 选民需要注册才能获得投票资格。
EN: Voters need to register to be eligible to vote.

ZH: 选民必须去投票站进行投票。
EN: Voters must go to the polling station to cast their votes.

ZH: 选民可以选择提前投票或当天投票。
EN: Voters can choose to vote early or on the day of the election.

ZH: 选民的票数会被计算在候选人的总数中。
EN: Voters' votes will be counted as part of the candidates' totals.

ZH: 选民可以通过电子投票系统进行投票。
EN: Voters can vote through electronic voting systems.

ZH: 选民应该研究候选人的政绩和承诺。
EN: Voters should research the candidates' track records and promises.

ZH: 选民可以通过投票纪录查询系统确认自己是否已经投票。
EN: Voters can use the voting record inquiry system to confirm if they have already voted.

ZH: 选民对候选人的信任度非常重要。
EN: Voters' trust in the candidates is crucial.

ZH: 选民可以通过选民登记表更新个人信息。
EN: Voters can update their personal information through voter registration forms.

ZH: 选民应该保护自己的选举权利。
EN: Voters should protect their right to vote.

ZH: 选民的意见和意愿应该得到尊重。
EN: Voters' opinions and wishes should be respected.

ZH: 选民的参与率对选举结果有很大影响。
EN: The voter turnout has a significant impact on the election results.
